// UBSVLAST.D
/* #14889 */
@4220 = ~He's out there. He's coming. I can feel his footsteps, following me. The scent of rotting flesh. He's coming for us all.~ 
/* #14890 */
@4221 = ~I-- I killed him. But he's out there, he's coming this way, I can f-- feel it.~ 
/* #14891 - MODIFIED */
@4222 = ~I was a paladin, once. I fought on the side of good but it all comes to naught... I murdered him in cold blood, my brother in the faith... When he comes, let him be.~ 
/* #14893 - MODIFIED */
@4223 = ~What have you done? Now I am twice as wretched! Kill me in this tortured place! At least there will be some justice then.~ 
/* #14894 */
@4224 = ~What could you ever hope to learn from a wretched fool like me? Learn from my example, at least, and seek not to kill that which is good in the world.~ 
/* #14895 */
@4225 = ~Please, just leave me to my misery.~ 
/* #14896 */
@4226 = ~Much as I may welcome death, I will not face it without a fight.~ 
@4227 = ~I am sorry, my brother... I was jealous, I was... a fool. My life is yours.~ 

// Replies
@4240 = ~What are you talking about? Who is coming for us?~
@4241 = ~Who was this person? Why does he hunt you from beyond the grave?~
@4242 = ~Are you mad? I will not simply stand by and let this creature kill you!~
@4243 = ~As you wish. I do not agree with your decision, but if it is your choice to die by this creature's hand, I will not stand in the way.~ 
@4244 = ~No problem. This is between you and him. I want no part of it!~
@4245 = ~An undead creature seeks *your* death? Perhaps we should just give it what it wants!~
@4246 = ~As you wish. Let justice be done.~
@4247 = ~I refuse. I will not be your executioner. You will have to atone for your crimes. Perhaps then others may learn from your mistakes.~ 
@4248 = ~That's a fine way to show show gratitude! I just saved your miserable life!~
@4249 = ~If that's what you desire, it will be my pleasure.~

// Journal Entries
//  (Strref: 15713)
@4290 = ~Svlast's Torment
I have been witness to sad events within the Firewine ruins. An ex-paladin by the name of Svlast is being hunted by the spirit of his brother in the faith, whom he wrongfully killed. Never have I seen a more dejected and repentant soul than poor Svlast. He has begged us not to interfere but my heart does not rest easy with such a choice...~
@4291 = ~Svlast's Torment
An ex-paladin by the name of Svlast is being hunted by the spirit of his brother in the faith, whom he wrongfully killed. He begged us not to interfere.~
@4292 = ~Svlast's Torment
An ex-paladin by the name of Svlast is being hunted by the spirit of his brother in the faith, whom he wrongfully killed. I gave the creature what it wants.~
@4293 = ~Svlast's Torment
Svlast's torment has ended. The creature took its revenge.~
